data.title: Info-Tech Research Group introduces a four-step framework for enterprise AI transformation to address struggles in strategy implementation.
data.description: Artificial intelligence has emerged as a highly impactful technology in recent times, accessible to many but posing challenges for organizations aiming to transition from experimental use to a structured enterprise strategy. Leading global research and advisory firm Info-Tech Research Group has conducted studies revealing this trend.

data.title: Increased use of thrombectomy for blood clots shown in Medicare data analysis from 2017-2022. Venous and arterial claims rose.
data.description: In Fairfax, Virginia, as of October 31, 2025, recent analysis of Medicare data revealed a significant rise in arterial and venous thrombectomy claims related to venous thromboembolic disease during the period from 2017 to 2022. A detailed examination of Medicare claims for arterial and venous thrombectomy procedures was conducted by researchers as part of the study.

data.title: RAYUS Radiology introduces Transpara® Breast AI in Washington State, advancing breast cancer detection with AI-assisted mammography.
data.description: RAYUS Radiology has recently unveiled a new AI-assisted mammography technology in its clinics located in Washington State as of October 31, 2025. With this advancement, patients can now benefit from one of the cutting-edge tools available for detecting breast cancer. The introduction of Transpara® Breast AI by RAYUS Radiology in Washington signifies a significant enhancement in their ability to provide top-tier healthcare services.

BCBSIL's latest plans offer a range of coverage options to meet various needs and preferences.

data.title: Blue Cross and Blue Shield of Texas offers health insurance plans in Texas as open enrollment begins Nov 1, 2025.
data.description: In Richardson, Texas, as of October 31, 2025, Blue Cross and Blue Shield of Texas (BCBSTX) is dedicated to providing high-quality health insurance plans for individuals and families in Texas. The open enrollment period is set to commence on November 1. BCBSTX aims to offer a range of health insurance options to cater to the diverse needs of the population.

data.title: Beale Infrastructure plans $1 billion investment in Tulsa County for new data center campus, boosting economy and infrastructure.
data.description: Beale Infrastructure revealed the commencement of construction on a cutting-edge data center campus in Tulsa County, Oklahoma. The project, dubbed Project Clydesdale, entails a substantial collaboration with both local and state authorities to bring sustainable economic growth and improved infrastructure to the area. With a significant commitment of $1 billion earmarked for this development, the initiative aims to bolster the regional power grid, upgrade public utilities, and generate employment prospects for residents of Oklahoma.

data.title: WOUFX LLC becomes first 100% Uzbek-owned company registered with U.S. SEC - historic milestone achieved.
data.description: In Wilmington, Delaware on October 31, 2025, WOUFX LLC successfully completed its registration with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), becoming the inaugural company in American history to be entirely owned by a citizen of Uzbekistan. This milestone makes WOUFX LLC the sole entity in the U.S. with this unique ownership distinction.

data.title: US firms partnering with AWS to boost AI and cloud adoption, says ISG in Stamford, Conn. $III #AI.
data.description: Businesses throughout the United States are collaborating with AWS and its partners to speed up cloud modernization efforts and quickly expand their utilization of AI, as per ISG reports.

data.title: SkinCure Oncology celebrates Radiation Therapists during National Radiologic Technology Week in 2025. #IGSRT #NMSC #BurrRidge
data.description: On October 31, 2025, SkinCure Oncology, based in Burr Ridge, Illinois, shared its innovative approach to treating nonmelanoma skin cancer (NMSC) using Image-Guided Superficial Radiation Therapy (IGSRT). The company is recognized as a pioneer in the industry for its comprehensive cancer center model. This therapy aims to deliver precise radiation treatment for NMSC patients.

data.title: Stephanie J. Bannister appointed as President of FirstGen Forward bringing experience in student affairs to support first-gen student success.
data.description: Dr. Bannister, a knowledgeable figure in student affairs and an expert on the obstacles faced by first-generation students, has been appointed to lead FirstGen Forward. This appointment comes amidst a crucial time for the movement. The announcement was made in Washington on October 31, 2025. Dr. Bannister's experience and understanding make her well-suited to guide FirstGen Forward as it addresses the challenges of first-generation student success.
